"{\"uid\": \"cbsnews.com-minnesota-news-regan-smith-wins-silver-medal-womens-100-meters-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Watch CBS News  Updated on:  July 30, 2024 / 4:16 PM CDT/ AP  Australia's Kaylee McKeown knocked off Minnesota native and world-record holder Regan Smith in the 100 back on Tuesday night inParis, defending the title she won at the Tokyo Games.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 243, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 58, \"end\": 60, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9639503828313083, \"rank\": 0.03739779299853321, \"text\": \"AP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}, {\"begin\": 62, \"end\": 71, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.96927699626943, \"rank\": 0.03108177351132692, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\"}, {\"begin\": 74, \"end\": 88, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaylee McKeown\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\"}, {\"begin\": 101, \"end\": 110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota_Golden_Gophers_men's_ice_hockey\", \"score\": 0.8286674933044245, \"rank\": 0.17788290521121222, \"text\": \"Minnesota\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota_Golden_Gophers_men's_ice_hockey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota_Golden_Gophers_men's_ice_hockey\"}, {\"begin\": 142, \"end\": 153, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.1234027447781555e-24, \"text\": \"Regan Smith\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regan_Smith\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Smith, whobroke McKeown's world mark with a time of 57.13 seconds at the U.S. trials last month, led at the turn but could not hold off the hard-charging Aussie, who defended the title she won in Tokyo three years ago.\", \"from\": 245, \"to\": 463, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 441, \"end\": 446, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9937314711469308, \"rank\": 0.0063080295234740485, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McKeown surged to the front about halfway through the return lap and reached for the wall in 57.33, winning by a relatively comfortable margin over Smith's finish of 57.66.\", \"from\": 465, \"to\": 637, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. also grabbed the bronze as Katharine Berkoff touched third in 57.98.\", \"from\": 639, \"to\": 716, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 675, \"end\": 692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katharine_Berkoff\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katharine Berkoff\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katharine_Berkoff\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katharine_Berkoff\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Smith reached over the lane rope to congratulate McKeown, but this one had to sting.\", \"from\": 717, \"to\": 801, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 22-year-old Minnesota native appeared to be in top form after her performance and primed to win the first gold medal of her career.\", \"from\": 802, \"to\": 937, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 818, \"end\": 827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota_Golden_Gophers_men's_ice_hockey\", \"score\": 0.8286674933044245, \"rank\": 0.17788290521121222, \"text\": \"Minnesota\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota_Golden_Gophers_men's_ice_hockey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota_Golden_Gophers_men's_ice_hockey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Smith reached over the lane rope to congratulate McKeown, but this one had to sting.\", \"from\": 939, \"to\": 1023, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 22-year-old appeared to be in top form after her performance and primed to win the first gold medal of her career.\", \"from\": 1024, \"to\": 1142, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, it was McKeown capturing her fourth gold.\", \"from\": 1144, \"to\": 1194, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She swept the backstroke events in Tokyo and also claimed a gold in a relay.\", \"from\": 1195, \"to\": 1271, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1230, \"end\": 1235, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9937314711469308, \"rank\": 0.0063080295234740485, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Daniel Wiffen won Ireland's first gold medal in swimming since scandal-plagued Michelle Smith finished first in three events at the 1996 Atlanta Olympics.\", \"from\": 1273, \"to\": 1427, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1291, \"end\": 1298, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9286341745437148, \"rank\": 0.05130858191402967, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 1352, \"end\": 1360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelle_Obama\", \"score\": 0.9756976033698972, \"rank\": 0.02216399220708409, \"text\": \"Michelle\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelle_Obama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelle_Obama\"}, {\"begin\": 1405, \"end\": 1426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1996_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 3.311406639811045e-13, \"text\": \"1996 Atlanta Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1996_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1996_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1410, \"end\": 1426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1996_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 3.2652009657668114e-13, \"text\": \"Atlanta Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1996_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1996_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wiffen surged past Italy's Gregorio Paltrinieri on the final lap, looking as fresh as he did at the beginning of the grueling race.\", \"from\": 1429, \"to\": 1560, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1448, \"end\": 1453, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9828063853158012, \"rank\": 0.017480572133707118, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1456, \"end\": 1476, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gregorio_Paltrinieri\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gregorio Paltrinieri\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gregorio_Paltrinieri\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gregorio_Paltrinieri\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wiffen won in 7 minutes, 38.19 seconds, climbing on the lane ropes to hold one finger skyward.\", \"from\": 1562, \"to\": 1656, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Defending Olympic champion Bobby Finke also came on strong in what was essentially a three-man race, also passing Paltrinieri to take the silver in 7:38.75.\", \"from\": 1657, \"to\": 1813, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1684, \"end\": 1695, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Finke\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bobby Finke\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Finke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Finke\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The bronze went to the Italian, who posted a time of 7:39.38.\", \"from\": 1815, \"to\": 1876, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1838, \"end\": 1845, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.8354487649409449, \"rank\": 0.19688838513587417, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was another dazzling performance by an Irish swimmer, on the heels of Mona McSharry grabbing a bronze in the 100 breaststroke the previous night.\", \"from\": 1878, \"to\": 2026, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1920, \"end\": 1925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9472613941620425, \"rank\": 0.045462468977771446, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 1951, \"end\": 1964, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mona_McSharry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mona McSharry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mona_McSharry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mona_McSharry\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Until these Olympics, the country's swimming history was essentially confined to Smith, who surprisingly claimed three golds and a bronze in 1996 amid